ons  fastest laps  first entry  united states grand prix last entry  australian grand prix mark blundell born  april  is a british racing driver who competed in formula one for  seasons sports cars and cart most notably he won the   hours of le mans he was a formula one presenter for the british broadcaster itv until the end of the  season when the tv broadcasting rights switched to the bbc contents  background  formula one  cart  from driving to commentating  helmet  racing record  complete international formula  results  complete japanese formula  championship results  complete  hours of le mans results  complete formula one results  complete cart results  complete american le mans series results  references  external links backgroundedit blundell was born in barnet london he first dabbled in motor racing at the age of  racing motocross bikes across england he was an immediate success eventually becoming one of the topranked riders in britain winning a few championships at the age of  he made the switch to four wheels in britains formula ford again he was rewarded with instant success and in his first season he placed second in both british junior formula ford championships despite  wins and  poles the following year mark won both the esso british and snetterton ff crowns the next year he upgraded his ride to the more powerful ff category and promptly won the bbc grandstand series he even returned to ff for the european championship racing taking pole and finishing fourth overall with  came another championship in ff this time the european title at this point in his career blundell decided it was time to take his continuing success and move on to international racing he bypassed the traditional stepping stone of formula three and started racing in formula  despite having to cope with an underfunded and underpowered car he showed incredible talent and strung together a series of promising results he even started a few races at formula three for tomstoyota showing ability there as well  meant a switch to the works lola team in f at that time one of the biggest teams in the series in a closely contested season blundell managed a very respectable sixth place in the final standings formula oneedit the following year he made a deal with the sports car team at nissan landing a factory seat he also managed a test drive with one of the top teams in formula one – williams by  blundell had abandoned f to concentrate on sports cars that same year he earned pole position at the prestigious le mans  hours race driving a nissan rck blundell became the youngest driver to achieve pole position at the le mans  hours with a second margin ahead of second place blundell driving for mclaren at the  british grand prix the year  marked blundells transition into formula one his debut season saw a sixth place in belgium with the brabham yamaha team he also maintained his testing deal with williams the following season however he was not retained by the cashstrapped brabham team and was left without a race seat in formula one he did however sign a testing deal with mclaren whilst being a fulltime tester for mclaren he also continued to race sports cars that year with the factory peugeot outfit he won the le mans  hours adding to his earlier pole  saw the return of mark blundell to the pinnacle of motorsport a drive with ligier netted him his first two podium finishes in south africa and germany he finished tenth in the final world championship standings it was a oneyear deal with ligier however and in  he signed with tyrrell it was not as successful a year as  and blundell managed only one podium finish in the  spanish grand prix which was the last formula one podium finish for tyrrell at the end of the season owing to lack of sponsorship tyrrell released him this would prove to be a blessing in disguise as the retirement of nigel mansell meant a return to mclaren for blundell this time in a race seat teamed with future twotime world champion mika häkkinen blundell recorded five points finishes and once again took tenth in the final standings  also saw continued success in sports cars with a fourth place showing in le mans but was mark blundells final year in formula one as the signing of david coulthard by mclaren meant that mark would have to find a job somewhere else blundell achieved  podiums and scored a total of  championship points cartedit mark blundell cart world series years active – teams pacwest racing starts  wins  poles  best finish th in  awards  autosport british driver of the year out of formula one blundell moved to the us and joined the cart racing team pacwest racing with fellow former formula one driver maurício gugelmin of brazil alongside a crash in the early stages of the season in rio resulting in a broken foot and ankle forced blundell to miss several races despite this mark was third in the rookie standings with three top six finishes in the us  detroit grand prix and michigan international speedway races  was a breakout year blundell came within one corner of winning the detroit belle isle grand prix before running out of fuel an event he described at the time as the worst disappointment of his career in the very next race he powered past gil de ferran on the final straight to win the grand prix of portland by  seconds blundell recorded further race victories in toronto and fontana en route to sixth in the championship that year he was also named british driver of the year by autosport magazine  was not a year for the books and a massive crash early in  left him to languish at the bottom of the table he returned to pacwest for a final season in  however another disappointing season –  pts st overall – lead to a mutual split with pacwest racing from driving to commentatingedit blundell again crossed the atlantic to focus on his sports car racing he failed to finish le mans with the mg lola team though he and his teammates impressed offtrack blundell joined itv television in britain as an analyst for the  formula one season this position lasted until the end of the  formula one season when itv lost coverage to the bbc since  blundells racing involvement has steadily declined with only the occasional event he did test a dale coyne champ car to help prepare darren manning for a oneoff in the first cart race in britain at rockingham and raced in the british round of the world rally championship  saw great success in sports cars along with johnny herbert and david brabham he finished second at the  hours of le mans completing a – sweep by bentley he also finished third at the  hours of sebring finishing top among the bentleys blundell also spends time running a management company mb partners who handle the contracts of such people as mclaren test driver gary paffett and british formula  champion and indycar driver mike conway the name refers to the fact that it was founded by blundell and former teammate martin brundle who stepped down from the company in january  in a newspaper article in  blundell was openly critical of oval racing in general and of the  izod indycar world championship which had claimed the life of dan wheldon helmetedit blundells helmet is yellow with three red stripes and two yellow gaps in the middle a blue stripe in the entire chin area and a blue circle on the top with his golden initials on it the rear of his helmet bears the motto the will to win  a quote from his grandfather racing recordedit complete international formula  resultsedit key races in bold indicate pole position races in italics indicate fastest lap year entrant            dc points  fleetray racing sil ret val  spa  pau don  brh  bir dnq th  bs automotive per  imo ret bug ret jar   lola motorsport jer  val  pau ret sil  mnz ret per ret brh  bir ret bug  zol  dij ret th   middlebridge sil  val ret pau  jer dnq per ret brh ret bir  spa dns bug ret dij  th  complete japanese formula  championship resultsedit key races in bold indicate pole position races in itali